休閒、文化、運動專題研究                 TRENDS IN LEISURE, CULTURE & SPORT


  	 This course engages students in a critical review of current research in leisure, sport and culture studies. Class discussions examine the theories and methods that are prominent in our field, uncover epistemological values and beliefs that have shaped that research, and introduce alternative paradigms that provide different understandings of those same topics. Students will strengthen their writing in relation to scholarly literature reviews and critique of the literature.This course engages students in a critical review of current research in leisure, sport and culture studies. Class discussions examine the theories and methods that are prominent in our field, uncover epistemological values and beliefs that have shaped that research, and introduce alternative paradigms that provide different understandings of those same topics. Students will strengthen their writing in relation to scholarly literature reviews and critique of the literature.

課程教育目標 

A 溝通能力 Communication Skills
(COMMU)B 創新及解決問題能力 Creative Problem Solving & Innovation
(CPSI)C 倫理道德與領導能力 Ethic & Leadership Skills
(ETHIC/LEAD)D 國際觀及批判能力 Global Awareness & Critical Thinking
(GLOB/CT) 
